## Articles and content (when blog exists in repo)

- **Path:** `src/content/articles/{slug}/index.mdx`, `imgs/`, optional `components/`
- **Rules:** `article-writing.mdc`, `content-pipeline.mdc`
- **Language:** Ukrainian for user-facing copy.
- **Topic:** computerized embroidery (Gapta / gapta.com.ua).
- **Git:** no direct commits to **`master`**; feature branches; `conventional-commits` skill.

## Git flow for new articles (Stage 5)

- **Branch from `master`:** `git checkout master && git pull origin master && git checkout -b article/{slug}`
- **Commit:** e.g. `feat(article): add …` or `content(article): update …`
- **Push:** `git push -u origin article/{slug}`
- **PR:** GitHub MCP `create_pull_request`: owner `AZANIR`, repo **`Gapta`**, base **`master`**, head = branch name. Create the PR after push for article/content work.
- **Publish:** merge to **`master`** → [.github/workflows/deploy.yml](.github/workflows/deploy.yml). Full guide: [.cursor/docs/FLOW.md](.cursor/docs/FLOW.md).

